      "content": "Right, I see those names. But some people argue that the environmental stuff like nutrition and schooling is just a surface level explanation and doesn't account for the actual biological data being discussed in some evolutionary psychology papers. Can you go into more detail about the specific biological or genetic arguments that proponents of these theories use to explain the gaps?",
